    <h1>Controller in MVC</h1>
    <hr />
    <p>The Controller in the MVC pattern is responsible for handling user input and managing the application's flow of data.</p>

    <h2>Main Responsibilities:</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Receives and processes user input from the View.</li>
        <li>Interacts with the Model to retrieve or update data.</li>
        <li>Controls the overall behavior and flow of the application.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>In an ASP.NET MVC application, Controllers are responsible for routing user requests to the appropriate actions and returning the corresponding View to display the results.</p>
